Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 529 877 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19 5 August 2020 As of today, a cumulative total of 529 877 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded. Case Data Province Total cases for 05 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 80400 15,2 Free State 25232 4,8 Gauteng 185282 35,0 KwaZulu-Natal 87798 16,6 Limpopo 9625 1,8 Mpumalanga 17135 3,2 North West 20686 3,9 Northern Cape 5638 1,1 Western Cape 98031 18,5 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 529877 100,0 Testing Data The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 113 191 with 34 989 new tests conducted since the last report. Sector Total tested  New tested  PRIVATE 1762979 57% 22112 63% PUBLIC 1350212 43% 12877 37% Total 3113191  34989  Reported Deaths and Recoveries Regrettably we report 414 new COVID-19 related deaths: 135 from Eastern Cape, 45 from Gauteng, 62 from KwaZulu Natal, 34 from Western Cape, 16 from Mpumalanga and 122 from the Free State. This brings the cumulative number of deaths to 9 298. We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The number of recoveries currently stands at 377 266 which translates to a recovery rate of 71%. The provincial breakdown is as follows: Province Deaths Recoveries Eastern Cape 1967 72570 Free State 327 10582 Gauteng 2313 129375 KwaZulu-Natal 1038 51857 Limpopo 90 5620 Mpumalanga 139 11632 North West 109 9243 Northern Cape 36 2859 Western Cape 3279 83528 Total 9298 377266  